abstract: John Hickenlooper said he would give “serious thought” to a Senate run, Beto O’Rourke reset the focus of his campaign and Stacey Abrams laid out her 2020 plans.
snippet: John Hickenlooper said he would give “serious thought” to a Senate run, Beto O’Rourke reset the focus of his campaign and Stacey Abrams laid out her 2020 plans.
lead_paragraph: Here’s our quick weekly catch-up on the presidential campaign and the field of 24 — well, make that 23 — candidates for the Democratic nomination.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Barack Obama was riding his call for generational change to the Democratic presidential nomination in the spring of 2008 when he began musing about potential running mates with aides traveling with him on the trail.

abstract: After the shooting in El Paso, Mr. O’Rourke decided to abandon his focus on early primary states and more directly confront the president over immigration and gun control.
snippet: After the shooting in El Paso, Mr. O’Rourke decided to abandon his focus on early primary states and more directly confront the president over immigration and gun control.
lead_paragraph: Beto O’Rourke introduced himself to the country as a changed candidate on Thursday, with his presidential campaign recast as a moral crusade against President Trump in the aftermath of a mass shooting in El Paso, his hometown.

headline_main: Beto O’Rourke’s New Approach to 2020: ‘Taking the Fight to Donald Trump’

abstract: Even as she demonstrates why she is a leading presidential candidate, Ms. Warren is facing persistent questions and doubts about whether she would be able to defeat President Trump.
snippet: Even as she demonstrates why she is a leading presidential candidate, Ms. Warren is facing persistent questions and doubts about whether she would be able to defeat President Trump.
lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — Senator Elizabeth Warren has built the most formidable campaign organization of any Democratic presidential candidate in the first nominating states, raised an impressive $25 million without holding high-dollar fund-raisers, and has risen steadily in Iowa and New Hampshire polls.

headline_main: These Four Candidates Are Scrambling to Make the Cut for the Next Democratic Debate
headline_print_headline: Desperate Drive to Claim Spot in Next Debate

abstract: Revisiting the blistering criticism from President Trump’s own party raises questions about whether the search for a killer line on Mr. Trump is a fool’s errand for Democrats in 2020.
snippet: Revisiting the blistering criticism from President Trump’s own party raises questions about whether the search for a killer line on Mr. Trump is a fool’s errand for Democrats in 2020.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has called President Trump an “existential threat” to the nation.

headline_print_headline: Democrats Seek an Apt Retort; Republicans Tried Them All

abstract: The New Jersey senator and a few other Democratic candidates are detouring from early-voting states to spend time in Detroit, Philadelphia and Milwaukee.
snippet: The New Jersey senator and a few other Democratic candidates are detouring from early-voting states to spend time in Detroit, Philadelphia and Milwaukee.
lead_paragraph: MILWAUKEE — An energized crowd of 500 packed into a mixed-use space here on a summer Sunday afternoon to hear a rousing stump speech from Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey, who was making the final stop in a 12-day campaign blitz in a state that won’t hold its primary until April.
